RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Two Races Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELMAR SUMMER chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid a bid from the three path coming around the turn and drew off in the lane, in hand at the wire. ELARY led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and chased the winner home in the stretch. BINOCHE tracked the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around around the bend and was outkicked in the lane while keeping on to the wire. LUCKY FREEDOM trailed the field through the early going, saved ground around the turn and passed tiring horses in the lane. LADYNESS was fractious in the gate, broke well and settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and faded from there. HONEYBUNNYBOOBOO raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, navigated the bend from the three path and tired in the stretch.

FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $100,000 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED IN 2022 - 2023. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVER EXPLAIN stumbled mildly leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. DRAMA CHORUS saved ground a round the first turn, led the field on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second turn, dug in in upper stretch and gave way late. PERFECT SPEIGHTY stalked the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second bend and improved position in the stretch. CANNON'S ROAR trailed the field while racing on the rail through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and gained ground mildly in the lane while never threatening. LIKE THE KING raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and faded in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRAIN WRECK chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and kicked clear late. SHUT IT CALI stalked the pace setter on the inside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the bend, dueled down the lane and gave way near the wire. LUNITA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and finished evenly while proving to be no match for the top two. DON'T ANNOY ME led the way on the inside up the backstretch, gave way from the two path coming off the turn and weakened further in the stretch. AFTER NOON KISSES raced in the middle of the pack between horses early, continued around the turn in the five path, swung wider still into the stretch and finished evenly while never threatening. STAR OF SARAH was pinched back leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and passed tiring horses in the lane. SUNSHINE GIRL raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the three and four path and faded from there. LA VILLANA raced at the back of the pack through the opening stages, navigated the turn from the four path and made no bid. LUCKY VAN HEMEL tracked the leaders between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the turn and continued to tire in the stretch.
